                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; first words (headings or parts of
                           headings) of constituent texts; directives for the ministers; name of the
                           ruling king; some of the musical notation signs above the lines;
                           abbreviations; elements of the punctuation signs and Ethiopic
                           numerals.
 
 The beginning parts of some of the texts are written
                           alternately in red and black lines (e. g., fols. 3r, 96ra, 101rab,
                           108va).</seg>
